com.langtoun.oastypes.impl

Class OASTypeImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.langtoun.oastypes.impl.OASTypeImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OASType
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OASArrayTypeImpl, OASBooleanTypeImpl, OASDateTimeTypeImpl, OASDateTypeImpl, OASNullTypeImpl, OASNumericTypeImpl, OASObjectTypeImpl, OASStringTypeImpl

    public class OASTypeImpl
extends Object
implements OASType
    Base class for OpenAPI Specification types derived from the Schema object provided by the KaiZen openapi-parser library.
    See Also:
    KaiZen-OpenApi-Parser

                      com.reprezen.jsonoverlay.Reference reference)
        Protected constructor for an OASTypeImpl base object.
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent of this type.
        mappedName - The name of the node that a schema is attached to. For top level schemas this is the name of the type.
        schemaType - The resolved schema type name.
        schema - The Schema that will be used to build the OASTypeImpl.
        reference - A Reference associated with the schema which may be null.

      • defaultValue

        public Object defaultValue()
        Description copied from interface: OASType
        The default value represents what would be assumed by the consumer of the input as the value of the schema if one is not provided. Unlike JSON Schema, the value MUST conform to the defined type for the Schema Object defined at the same level. For example, if type is string, then default can be "foo" but cannot be 1.
        Specified by:
        defaultValue in interface OASType
        Returns:
        The value of the default node, or {code null} if it is missing.

      • readOnly

        public Boolean readOnly()
        Description copied from interface: OASType
        Relevant only for Schema "properties" definitions. Declares the property as "read only". This means that it MAY be sent as part of a response but SHOULD NOT be sent as part of the request. If the property is marked as readOnly being true and is in the required list, the required will take effect on the response only. A property MUST NOT be marked as both readOnly and writeOnly being true. Default value is false.
        Specified by:
        readOnly in interface OASType
        Returns:
        The value of the readOnly node, or {code null} if it is missing.

      • writeOnly

        public Boolean writeOnly()
        Description copied from interface: OASType
        Relevant only for Schema "properties" definitions. Declares the property as "write only". Therefore, it MAY be sent as part of a request but SHOULD NOT be sent as part of the response. If the property is marked as writeOnly being true and is in the required list, the required will take effect on the request only. A property MUST NOT be marked as both readOnly and writeOnly being true. Default value is false.
        Specified by:
        writeOnly in interface OASType
        Returns:
        The value of the writeOnly node, or {code null} if it is missing.
